# shadcn/ui Component Guidelines

## Setup and Configuration
- Components are located in `@/components/ui/`
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- Follow the established design tokens and CSS variables
- Maintain consistency with the global theme configuration

## Component Usage Patterns

### Form Components
```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input"
import { Label } from "@/components/ui/label"
import { Select, SelectContent, SelectItem, SelectTrigger, SelectValue } from "@/components/ui/select"

// Use with proper form patterns
<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
  <Input id="email" type="email" placeholder="Enter your email" />
</div>
```

### Dialog and Modal Patterns
```typescript
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogTrigger } from "@/components/ui/dialog"

// Always include proper accessibility attributes
<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger asChild>
    <Button>Open Dialog</Button>
  </DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>
    <DialogHeader>
      <DialogTitle>Dialog Title</DialogTitle>
    </DialogHeader>
    {/* Content */}
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

## Styling Guidelines
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- Prefer Tailwind classes over custom CSS when possible
- Use CSS variables for theme colors: `hsl(var(--primary))`
- Follow the established spacing scale (space-y-4, gap-4, etc.)

## Accessibility
- Always include proper ARIA attributes
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works correctly
- Include proper focus management for interactive components

## Common Patterns
- Use `asChild` prop when wrapping components
- Implement loading and disabled states consistently
- Handle form validation with proper error states
- Use the established color variants (default, destructive, outline, secondary, ghost)